### Example 1: Create Reusable Filter

This example shows you how to create a reusable filter.

```php
use GanbaroDigital\MissingBits\ClassesAndObjects\FilterClassProperties;

$filter = FilterClassProperties::using(
    ReflectionProperty::IS_PROTECTED | ReflectionProperty::IS_PRIVATE
);

var_dump($filter->filterClassProperties(ExampleClass::class));
var_dump($filter->filterClassProperties(FilterClassProperties::class));
```
The code above produces this output on PHP v5.6.30, PHP v7.0.20, PHP v7.1.6:

```
array(4) {
  ["value2"]=>
  string(28) "I am protected static value2"
  ["value3"]=>
  string(26) "I am private static value3"
  ["trait2"]=>
  string(28) "I am protected static trait2"
  ["trait3"]=>
  string(26) "I am private static trait3"
}
array(0) {
}
```
